  "prompt": "Why is development ethics important?",
  "response": "Development ethics is important for several key reasons:\n\n1. Moral considerations in development\n- Ensures human rights and dignity are prioritized\n- Addresses ethical implications of development policies and practices\n- Promotes social justice and equitable growth\n\n2. Addressing power dynamics\n- Challenges unequal power relationships\n- Gives voice to marginalized communities\n- Promotes inclusive and participatory development approaches\n\n3. Sustainable and holistic progress\n- Goes beyond economic metrics\n- Considers human well-being and environmental sustainability\n- Emphasizes quality of life, not just economic growth\n\n4. Preventing exploitation\n- Protects vulnerable populations\n- Ensures development doesn't harm local communities\n- Promotes responsible and ethical interventions\n\n5. Promoting human capabilities\n- Focuses on expanding individual and collective potential\n- Supports personal freedoms and opportunities\n- Encourages human-centered development strategies\n\n6. Ethical decision-making\n- Provides frameworks for evaluating development interventions\n- Helps balance competing interests and values\n- Supports more responsible and accountable development practices\n\n7. Global interconnectedness\n- Recognizes interdependence of global communities\n- Promotes cross-cultural understanding\n- Encourages collaborative and respectful development approaches\n\nDevelopment ethics ensures that progress is not just measured in economic terms, but also in human and moral dimensions.",
